1
00:00:01,562 --> 00:00:04,255
<i>Four weeks ago,
an invisible dome crashed down</i>

2
00:00:04,290 --> 00:00:08,140
<i>on Chester's Mill, cutting us
off from the rest of the world.</i>

3
00:00:08,175 --> 00:00:10,365
<i>The dome has tested
our limits,</i>

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,160
forcing each of us to confront
<i>our own personal demons...</i>

5
00:00:14,195 --> 00:00:15,696
<i>rage...</i>

6
00:00:15,698 --> 00:00:18,031
<i>grief...</i>

7
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:19,766
<i>fear.</i>

8
00:00:19,768 --> 00:00:20,968
My God.

9
00:00:22,404 --> 00:00:23,856
<i>Now, in order to survive,</i>

10
00:00:23,891 --> 00:00:26,840
<i>we must battle our most
dangerous adversary...</i>

11
00:00:26,842 --> 00:00:29,409
<i>the enemy within.</i>

12
00:00:29,411 --> 00:00:32,309
You saved me from
becoming one of them.

13
00:00:32,344 --> 00:00:34,047
I knew the real you
was still in there.

14
00:00:34,049 --> 00:00:35,916
The dome's surface
is calcifying,

15
00:00:35,918 --> 00:00:37,851
unless I can bring down
the dome with Joe's help.

16
00:00:37,853 --> 00:00:39,386
I have to stay
and build this device.

17
00:00:39,388 --> 00:00:40,486
It's the only
way out of here.

18
00:00:40,488 --> 00:00:42,591
<i>Everything has a cycle,</i>

19
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:44,490
and mine is
coming to an end.

20
00:00:44,492 --> 00:00:46,170
- Who the hell are you?!
- Hektor Martin.

21
00:00:46,205 --> 00:00:47,259
He runs Aktaion.

22
00:00:47,261 --> 00:00:48,203
I'm gonna do whatever it takes

23
00:00:48,238 --> 00:00:50,162
to make sure that
this dome never comes down.

24
00:00:50,164 --> 00:00:52,264
You're a threat
to Eva's baby, Julia.

25
00:00:52,299 --> 00:00:53,566
Gua...!

26
00:01:06,513 --> 00:01:09,281
No one saw us, right?

27
00:01:09,283 --> 00:01:11,917
I don't think so.

28
00:01:17,681 --> 00:01:18,282
Easy.

29
00:01:18,317 --> 00:01:19,449
Here.

30
00:01:21,293 --> 00:01:23,381
What the hell were you thinking,
sneaking off like that?

31
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:25,063
You're not my dad.
I can do what I want.

32
00:01:25,065 --> 00:01:26,839
Oh, sass?
Now we get sass?

33
00:01:26,874 --> 00:01:28,878
Look, your actions
affect all of us.

34
00:01:28,913 --> 00:01:30,634
You could've led those
freaks straight here to us.

35
00:01:30,636 --> 00:01:31,936
Which she didn't, okay?

36
00:01:31,938 --> 00:01:33,510
She saved my life,
so take it easy.

37
00:01:33,545 --> 00:01:34,972
We've got bigger
problems, anyway.

38
00:01:34,974 --> 00:01:36,574
Oh, you mean Barbie?

39
00:01:36,576 --> 00:01:39,383
Did his little side piece,
lure him back to alien town?

40
00:01:39,418 --> 00:01:42,523
No, but their baby is gonna be
here sooner than we thought.

41
00:01:42,558 --> 00:01:44,048
Norrie and I
just saw her.

42
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:46,352
She looks almost full-term.

43
00:01:46,838 --> 00:01:48,618
And I'm pretty sure
12 girls just died

44
00:01:48,620 --> 00:01:51,223
to make it the world's
shortest pregnancy.

45
00:01:52,756 --> 00:01:54,691
Well, then,
we got to kill her.

46
00:01:56,327 --> 00:01:58,335
We got to put her down
before that thing comes out.

47
00:01:58,370 --> 00:02:00,094
Why is that your solution
to everything?

48
00:02:00,129 --> 00:02:01,130
Killing the problem.

49
00:02:01,165 --> 00:02:02,754
I'm sure you like
stepping on spiders too.

50
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:05,934
Well, if the spider has
a queen baby inside

51
00:02:05,936 --> 00:02:08,604
that's gonna wipe out
the entire human race,

52
00:02:08,606 --> 00:02:11,216
that kind of spider, yeah,
I think I'd kill it.

53
00:02:11,251 --> 00:02:14,276
This cure of yours,
you really think it'll work?

54
00:02:14,278 --> 00:02:15,401
You said you didn't need it.

55
00:02:15,436 --> 00:02:17,359
I believe you said
love was the answer.

56
00:02:17,394 --> 00:02:20,000
And now I'm admitting
that might not be enough.

57
00:02:20,035 --> 00:02:21,548
Glad to hear it.

58
00:02:21,583 --> 00:02:23,937
Dr. Bloom has already
synthesized a base formula.

59
00:02:23,972 --> 00:02:26,144
All we need now is a specimen

60
00:02:26,179 --> 00:02:27,752
of Christine
Price's DNA.

61
00:02:27,787 --> 00:02:30,215
You'll need a test subject
to try it on, right?

62
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:32,127
I can be your lab monkey.

63
00:02:32,129 --> 00:02:34,029
Well, that's very
generous of you...

64
00:02:34,031 --> 00:02:36,031
but it's necessary
to have a subject

65
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:37,532
in whom the infection
is full-blown.

66
00:02:37,534 --> 00:02:38,872
I have a question.

67
00:02:38,907 --> 00:02:41,797
Joe, he's working on this thing
to bring the dome down...

68
00:02:41,832 --> 00:02:45,607
what if he finishes it before
you can get this cure to work?

69
00:02:45,609 --> 00:02:48,042
What if they get out?

70
00:02:48,044 --> 00:02:50,345
Well, then we have a
bunch of creepy-crawlies,

71
00:02:50,347 --> 00:02:52,046
that can have babies
in three days,

72
00:02:52,048 --> 00:02:54,182
going forth and prospering.

73
00:02:54,184 --> 00:02:55,844
That's not
gonna happen.

74
00:02:55,879 --> 00:02:58,253
I told you I'd get you
Christine Price's DNA...

75
00:02:58,255 --> 00:03:00,455
I'll get it.

76
00:03:00,457 --> 00:03:02,211
Christine was
at the barn with Eva.

77
00:03:02,246 --> 00:03:04,159
Better to go there than
Town Hall... I'll go with you.

78
00:03:04,161 --> 00:03:05,546
- Jim.
- Yeah.

79
00:03:05,581 --> 00:03:07,394
It's our last chance.

80
00:03:15,837 --> 00:03:18,356
All right,
nice and easy.

81
00:03:24,012 --> 00:03:26,579
Lay down, rest.

82
00:03:29,617 --> 00:03:31,974
Are you ready?

83
00:03:32,009 --> 00:03:33,677
For what?

84
00:03:33,712 --> 00:03:35,885
The new queen.

85
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,590
Of course.

86
00:03:39,026 --> 00:03:41,194
Get some sleep.

87
00:04:11,257 --> 00:04:12,357
You all right?

88
00:04:12,359 --> 00:04:13,991
Fine.

89
00:04:13,993 --> 00:04:16,194
I just stood up
too fast.

90
00:04:17,463 --> 00:04:20,134
How is Joe's work
progressing?

91
00:04:20,169 --> 00:04:23,268
He was initially resistant,
but he's come around.

92
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:26,272
He moved into a larger room, and
he's made a few breakthroughs.

93
00:04:26,307 --> 00:04:29,453
But... he's still in
the planning stage.

94
00:04:29,488 --> 00:04:30,875
We're running out of time.

95
00:04:30,877 --> 00:04:32,309
The dome is dying.

96
00:04:32,311 --> 00:04:33,824
If we don't get out
before it does...

97
00:04:33,859 --> 00:04:35,131
I can make him work faster.

98
00:04:35,166 --> 00:04:36,580
No.

99
00:04:36,582 --> 00:04:38,515
No violence.

100
00:04:38,517 --> 00:04:39,884
He's too valuable.

101
00:04:39,886 --> 00:04:41,418
I'll handle him.

102
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:43,681
- Have you seen Junior?
- I haven't.

103
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:46,729
But anything you need,
I can take care of.

104
00:04:46,764 --> 00:04:50,500
Joe will need our last remaining
amethyst to continue his work.

105
00:04:50,929 --> 00:04:53,811
I'll find a way to get
it up to him safely.

106
00:04:54,398 --> 00:04:57,067
You've come a long way, Sam.

107
00:04:57,069 --> 00:04:59,453
I'm pleased.

108
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:07,262
Barbie, how's Eva?

109
00:05:07,297 --> 00:05:09,442
She's resting,
comfortably.

110
00:05:09,477 --> 00:05:11,481
Good.

111
00:05:11,483 --> 00:05:14,126
The baby should be here
within the day.

112
00:05:18,188 --> 00:05:22,819
I'd like to go after what's
left of the Resistance.

113
00:05:22,854 --> 00:05:24,059
No need.

114
00:05:24,061 --> 00:05:28,662
Our primary concerns, right now,
are here, under this roof:

115
00:05:28,697 --> 00:05:32,662
the birth of the new queen
and the building of the device.

116
00:05:32,697 --> 00:05:35,450
They still pose a threat.

117
00:05:35,485 --> 00:05:37,454
Are you worried about
your daughter, Barbie?

118
00:05:37,489 --> 00:05:39,342
No.

119
00:05:39,344 --> 00:05:41,387
Only the kinship.

120
00:05:42,525 --> 00:05:44,987
Inside Eva is the queen

121
00:05:45,022 --> 00:05:47,405
who will lead our kinship
out of the dome.

122
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:50,104
Nothing is more
important than that.

123
00:05:51,421 --> 00:05:56,515
Your priority is to be by Eva's
side until that baby is born.

124
00:05:57,961 --> 00:06:00,162
I understand.

125
00:06:01,597 --> 00:06:03,999
There's aliens outside
the dome now, too.

126
00:06:04,001 --> 00:06:06,441
Not aliens, plural, like
the James Cameron sequel;

127
00:06:06,476 --> 00:06:08,542
alien, singular, like
the Ridley Scott original.

128
00:06:08,577 --> 00:06:11,405
Pretty sure this is
an isolated incident.

129
00:06:11,407 --> 00:06:11,963
I don't even know

130
00:06:11,998 --> 00:06:13,550
what I'm looking at here.

131
00:06:13,585 --> 00:06:16,477
That's Lily's dad,
or what used to be.

132
00:06:16,479 --> 00:06:18,779
Okay. And...?

133
00:06:18,781 --> 00:06:21,067
She doesn't know; she thinks
he's dead, but he's not...

134
00:06:21,102 --> 00:06:23,923
he's in some Aktaion
containment unit in Zenith.

135
00:06:23,958 --> 00:06:25,738
Well, does that
Hektor guy know?

136
00:06:25,773 --> 00:06:26,802
He's got to, right?

137
00:06:26,837 --> 00:06:29,772
I-I mean, he's the one who told
Lily to destroy these files.

138
00:06:29,807 --> 00:06:31,026
- We should tell her.
- Wait, wait, wait.

139
00:06:31,061 --> 00:06:33,028
Just telling her out of the
blue, it could mess her up.

140
00:06:33,063 --> 00:06:34,694
And Hektor...

141
00:06:34,696 --> 00:06:37,231
maybe he's got a reason for
keeping this on the down low.

142
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:38,899
Seriously?

143
00:06:38,901 --> 00:06:40,234
You're defending him?

144
00:06:40,236 --> 00:06:41,990
No, I'm just saying

145
00:06:42,025 --> 00:06:44,238
maybe we run it by Julia
before we do anything.

146
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,273
Are you okay?

147
00:06:46,275 --> 00:06:48,692
Yeah. Why?

148
00:06:48,727 --> 00:06:52,345
I don't know, what Julia said
before, that you saved her.

149
00:06:52,347 --> 00:06:55,014
What happened out there?

150
00:06:55,016 --> 00:06:56,948
Nothing, I'm fine.

151
00:07:01,168 --> 00:07:02,355
Hey, there you are.

152
00:07:02,357 --> 00:07:03,857
Check this out.

153
00:07:03,859 --> 00:07:05,838
Okay, so you know the whistling
the town's been doing?

154
00:07:05,873 --> 00:07:07,480
The amethyst responds to it.

155
00:07:07,515 --> 00:07:08,632
- That's great, Joe.
- The strange thing is:

156
00:07:08,667 --> 00:07:11,579
it only actually responds
when you're whistling to it.

157
00:07:11,614 --> 00:07:12,698
Look, look.

158
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,205
Okay, it lights up, yeah?

159
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,158
Okay, now watch.

160
00:07:23,444 --> 00:07:24,718
It doesn't respond
to a recording.

161
00:07:24,753 --> 00:07:26,854
- Okay, that's-that's fascinating.
- But how does it know that?

162
00:07:26,889 --> 00:07:28,588
- I mean, it's got to detect a...
- Okay, Joe, Joe.

163
00:07:28,623 --> 00:07:30,131
Slow down.

164
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:32,833
I need to know how soon
until this thing is working.

165
00:07:32,868 --> 00:07:35,917
I don't know, I-I have a couple
big problems to figure out.

166
00:07:35,952 --> 00:07:37,118
A day or two?

167
00:07:37,153 --> 00:07:38,706
I need you to stall.

168
00:07:38,741 --> 00:07:39,648
What?

169
00:07:39,683 --> 00:07:41,522
No, I-I thought the dome
needed to come down

170
00:07:41,557 --> 00:07:42,437
before we choked to death.

171
00:07:42,472 --> 00:07:45,162
It-it does, but the Resistance
is working on a cure.

172
00:07:45,164 --> 00:07:48,672
We have to see if it'll work
before your device does.

173
00:07:48,707 --> 00:07:52,060
Otherwise we unleash the kinship
on the rest of the world.

174
00:07:52,095 --> 00:07:52,728
Okay.

175
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:54,538
I'll-I'll try my best.

176
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:56,509
What are you gonna do?

177
00:07:56,544 --> 00:07:58,675
I'm gonna try and save Eva.

178
00:07:58,677 --> 00:08:00,112
The Eva I used to know.

179
00:08:00,147 --> 00:08:02,246
Barbie, be careful.

180
00:08:02,248 --> 00:08:04,629
These aliens, you got
'em tricked for now,

181
00:08:04,664 --> 00:08:07,604
but at some point, they'll
find out you're you.

182
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:11,892
Found a sample
of Christine's hair.

183
00:08:11,927 --> 00:08:13,490
Good.

184
00:08:13,492 --> 00:08:16,701
So the last time you saw Barbie
was here at the barn,

185
00:08:16,736 --> 00:08:18,195
he was walking away
with Miss,

186
00:08:18,230 --> 00:08:20,096
Barefoot and Ready-to-Pop?

187
00:08:20,098 --> 00:08:22,098
You sure he's still playing
for the home team?

188
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,767
Look, the only reason
that he's with her now

189
00:08:23,769 --> 00:08:25,602
is 'cause he cares about
what happens to his baby.

190
00:08:25,604 --> 00:08:26,732
Oh, I see.

191
00:08:26,767 --> 00:08:29,138
Just yesterday, you were all,
"Love conquers all."

192
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,942
And now you're, like,
"Rah, rah, cure"?

193
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:32,845
There's more to it than that.

194
00:08:33,177 --> 00:08:35,691
Barbie says the dome
is calcifying.

195
00:08:35,726 --> 00:08:37,694
Pretty soon, there won't
be any air to breathe.

196
00:08:37,729 --> 00:08:38,585
Does Hektor know about this?

197
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:40,530
- I don't think so.
- Well...

198
00:08:40,565 --> 00:08:42,908
if we're all gonna suffocate,
what's the point of a cure?

199
00:08:42,943 --> 00:08:44,138
If the cure works,

200
00:08:44,173 --> 00:08:45,721
and Joe figures out how
to take down the dome,

201
00:08:45,723 --> 00:08:48,449
maybe we can all get out of
here the same way we came in.

202
00:08:48,484 --> 00:08:50,589
Oh, human, you mean?

203
00:08:53,897 --> 00:08:56,443
Kill them.

204
00:08:59,035 --> 00:09:00,957
Hey, don't shoot!

205
00:09:00,992 --> 00:09:03,261
Stop! Don't shoot my son!

206
00:09:06,208 --> 00:09:09,076
I think we just found
our test subject.

207
00:09:17,486 --> 00:09:20,986
3x11 - <i>Love is a Battlefield</i>

208
00:09:25,769 --> 00:09:27,556
How long will it take
for the cure to be ready?

209
00:09:27,591 --> 00:09:29,533
Not long at all,
providing you stop hovering

210
00:09:29,568 --> 00:09:31,949
and let me extract the
DNA from this hair.

211
00:09:35,563 --> 00:09:37,155
That too tight for you?

212
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:38,999
Wait, scratch that.

213
00:09:39,001 --> 00:09:40,167
I don't care.

214
00:09:40,169 --> 00:09:42,089
You will later.

215
00:09:48,910 --> 00:09:50,365
We're gonna fix you, kid.

216
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,472
I've already been fixed.

217
00:09:52,507 --> 00:09:53,678
In the cocoons.

218
00:09:53,713 --> 00:09:54,963
They made me better.

219
00:09:54,998 --> 00:09:55,585
No, they didn't.

220
00:09:55,620 --> 00:09:59,613
They... they made you into
something I don't recognize.

221
00:09:59,648 --> 00:10:02,288
'Cause you're too shortsighted
to comprehend it.

222
00:10:02,290 --> 00:10:04,023
All I am

223
00:10:04,025 --> 00:10:06,426
is what the kinship
needs me to be,

224
00:10:06,428 --> 00:10:09,142
what this world
needs me to be.

225
00:10:09,177 --> 00:10:11,974
Junior, that sounds like...

226
00:10:12,009 --> 00:10:13,733
helter skelter to me.

227
00:10:15,470 --> 00:10:18,002
You don't know what's coming.

228
00:10:18,004 --> 00:10:21,248
You better hope
this cure doesn't work.

229
00:10:21,283 --> 00:10:22,154
Why?

230
00:10:22,189 --> 00:10:23,558
Because when the dome
comes down,

231
00:10:23,593 --> 00:10:26,239
you'll need the kinship
to survive.

232
00:10:27,213 --> 00:10:29,714
Survive what?

233
00:10:29,749 --> 00:10:31,348
Can I show you something?

234
00:10:31,383 --> 00:10:33,084
Julia...

235
00:10:33,086 --> 00:10:34,996
this is important.

236
00:10:51,936 --> 00:10:53,270
Enjoying yourself?

237
00:10:53,272 --> 00:10:54,405
Yeah,

238
00:10:54,407 --> 00:10:57,112
it was all there was
to listen to.

239
00:10:57,442 --> 00:10:59,176
Listening to music

240
00:10:59,178 --> 00:11:02,453
instead of working
on our special little project?

241
00:11:03,652 --> 00:11:05,485
I was thinking,

242
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:07,407
I'm not like
one of your drones.

243
00:11:07,442 --> 00:11:09,593
I can't just work
until I drop.

244
00:11:09,628 --> 00:11:13,362
Sometimes I got to stop thinking
in order to think.

245
00:11:13,591 --> 00:11:15,057
Besides,

246
00:11:15,059 --> 00:11:16,959
I-I hit a problem.

247
00:11:16,961 --> 00:11:19,061
The original plan

248
00:11:19,063 --> 00:11:22,617
was to have the amethyst
conduct the tones into the egg,

249
00:11:22,652 --> 00:11:24,400
which would act as a key,

250
00:11:24,402 --> 00:11:26,368
signaling the dome to unlock.

251
00:11:26,370 --> 00:11:29,446
Of course, that requires
seven amethysts and the egg,

252
00:11:29,481 --> 00:11:31,951
both of which
Big Jim destroyed.

253
00:11:31,986 --> 00:11:34,854
So we don't have
enough amethysts,

254
00:11:34,889 --> 00:11:37,279
and we don't have a way to
transmit a signal to the dome?

255
00:11:37,281 --> 00:11:38,770
Those are some big problems.

256
00:11:38,805 --> 00:11:39,948
Come on, Joe...

257
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:42,622
I know you better than that.

258
00:11:42,657 --> 00:11:45,887
I know you find
the problem exciting.

259
00:11:45,889 --> 00:11:48,396
First things first.

260
00:11:48,431 --> 00:11:52,035
We need to split the amethyst
into seven pieces.

261
00:11:52,070 --> 00:11:53,561
How?

262
00:11:53,563 --> 00:11:55,396
I have no idea.

263
00:11:55,431 --> 00:11:56,666
Come with me.

264
00:11:56,701 --> 00:11:59,104
There's something
you need to see.

265
00:12:01,037 --> 00:12:02,569
How are you?

266
00:12:04,506 --> 00:12:06,635
I'm tired.

267
00:12:06,808 --> 00:12:09,014
And weak.

268
00:12:15,850 --> 00:12:18,152
How are you feeling?

269
00:12:18,154 --> 00:12:19,843
I just told you I was tired.

270
00:12:19,878 --> 00:12:24,157
No, I mean about the girls
in the barn...

271
00:12:24,159 --> 00:12:26,526
and the sacrifice
that they made.

272
00:12:26,528 --> 00:12:29,362
They did their duty.

273
00:12:29,364 --> 00:12:34,015
Just like I'm doing mine, being
a vessel for the new queen.

274
00:12:38,238 --> 00:12:42,639
You remember how badly
you wanted to have a baby?

275
00:12:43,478 --> 00:12:44,894
How affected you were

276
00:12:44,929 --> 00:12:47,590
when you found out
you weren't pregnant?

277
00:12:50,384 --> 00:12:52,870
I remember.

278
00:12:55,356 --> 00:12:58,085
But that Eva's gone.

279
00:12:58,258 --> 00:13:00,459
It doesn't matter
what I want.

280
00:13:00,494 --> 00:13:03,480
All that matters is what's best
for the group.

281
00:13:05,932 --> 00:13:08,868
This isn't our child.

282
00:13:08,870 --> 00:13:11,696
This child belongs
to the kinship.

283
00:13:15,208 --> 00:13:16,688
This was Patrick
four days ago?

284
00:13:16,711 --> 00:13:19,167
According to
the time stamp, yeah.

285
00:13:19,202 --> 00:13:21,097
So he's lying.

286
00:13:25,285 --> 00:13:26,585
It's ready to go.

287
00:13:26,587 --> 00:13:28,353
You are <i>not</i> using this.

288
00:13:28,355 --> 00:13:29,755
What's going on here?

289
00:13:29,757 --> 00:13:31,023
I was about to ask
the same thing.

290
00:13:31,025 --> 00:13:33,058
What aren't you telling us
about Patrick Walters?

291
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:35,212
About my father?

292
00:13:37,863 --> 00:13:41,139
He's still alive.

293
00:13:42,801 --> 00:13:44,102
No.

294
00:13:44,104 --> 00:13:46,738
That's not possible.

295
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:48,940
He's dead.

296
00:13:50,109 --> 00:13:51,848
You told me he's dead.

297
00:13:51,883 --> 00:13:53,481
He's not dead, sweetheart,

298
00:13:53,516 --> 00:13:54,879
but he is gone.

299
00:13:54,881 --> 00:13:57,048
What does that even mean?

300
00:13:57,050 --> 00:13:58,441
I think you
should have Hunter

301
00:13:58,476 --> 00:14:00,365
show you the video.

302
00:14:03,422 --> 00:14:05,529
I'd like to know what video
you're referring to.

303
00:14:05,564 --> 00:14:08,059
I'm sure you would, but I'm
asking the questions now.

304
00:14:08,061 --> 00:14:10,525
So before you
stick this in Junior,

305
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:11,754
why don't you tell us
what really happened

306
00:14:11,789 --> 00:14:13,502
to your good friend Patrick.

307
00:14:13,537 --> 00:14:15,699
The only reason I kept
Patrick's condition a secret

308
00:14:15,701 --> 00:14:17,358
was for Lily's sake.
I didn't want to hurt her.

309
00:14:17,393 --> 00:14:19,270
Condition?

310
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:25,091
He turned into something else,
something other.

311
00:14:25,126 --> 00:14:26,477
A kind of energy infused

312
00:14:26,479 --> 00:14:27,971
with consciousness,

313
00:14:28,006 --> 00:14:30,314
but it wasn't his.

314
00:14:30,316 --> 00:14:31,968
It was <i>their</i> consciousness.

315
00:14:32,003 --> 00:14:34,048
All right, so your
main man Marston,

316
00:14:34,083 --> 00:14:36,553
he was working on a cure
to save your friend...

317
00:14:36,555 --> 00:14:38,188
but it didn't work?

318
00:14:41,358 --> 00:14:43,393
Well, so who's to say this stuff

319
00:14:43,395 --> 00:14:45,796
won't do the same thing
to my son?

320
00:14:47,411 --> 00:14:49,199
I'll be honest, Jim...

321
00:14:49,201 --> 00:14:50,500
it could.

322
00:14:50,502 --> 00:14:53,030
But I believe it will work.

323
00:14:53,065 --> 00:14:55,552
The advances we've made
since Patrick was lost,

324
00:14:55,587 --> 00:14:57,378
the opportunities
we had to derive

325
00:14:57,413 --> 00:14:58,977
a pure strain
from Christine,

326
00:14:59,012 --> 00:15:00,443
this is the best shot
at treatment

327
00:15:00,445 --> 00:15:01,760
that we've ever had.

328
00:15:01,795 --> 00:15:04,638
We have the briefest of windows
to save this town.

329
00:15:04,673 --> 00:15:05,541
Like you said, Julia,

330
00:15:05,576 --> 00:15:08,830
to get the infection out of
Hunter, Norrie, Barbie...

331
00:15:08,865 --> 00:15:10,099
if the cure succeeds...

332
00:15:10,134 --> 00:15:12,243
out of my friend as well.

333
00:15:14,158 --> 00:15:17,259
It's up to you, Jim.

334
00:15:17,261 --> 00:15:19,998
He's your son, not mine.

335
00:15:21,297 --> 00:15:23,271
It could kill him.

336
00:15:23,306 --> 00:15:24,933
There's a risk, of course.

337
00:15:24,935 --> 00:15:27,902
But if we don't try...

338
00:15:27,936 --> 00:15:30,530
there certainly
won't be a reward.

339
00:15:33,909 --> 00:15:36,177
Do it.

340
00:15:50,127 --> 00:15:52,228
Where are we going?

341
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:56,873
If this is
about the dome calcifying,

342
00:15:56,908 --> 00:15:58,071
I already know.

343
00:15:58,106 --> 00:16:00,430
I need your cooperation.

344
00:16:00,465 --> 00:16:02,361
Cooperation.

345
00:16:02,396 --> 00:16:05,447
Seems to me you've only asked
for my submission.

346
00:16:05,741 --> 00:16:08,249
Oh, I see.

347
00:16:08,284 --> 00:16:10,920
You still think
we want to be here.

348
00:16:10,955 --> 00:16:12,995
That we wanted to travel
hundreds of thousands

349
00:16:13,030 --> 00:16:15,648
of light-years through
a cold, harsh vacuum,

350
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:17,885
that we wanted
to leave our home,

351
00:16:17,887 --> 00:16:20,564
our history behind.

352
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:23,757
Earth is a wonderful place,

353
00:16:23,759 --> 00:16:28,051
but it's not that great.

354
00:16:28,086 --> 00:16:29,689
Why are you here?

355
00:16:29,724 --> 00:16:32,346
Because we had no choice.

356
00:16:32,381 --> 00:16:34,249
And now, neither do you.

357
00:16:34,284 --> 00:16:35,668
Right now,

358
00:16:35,670 --> 00:16:38,426
somewhere, up in the sky,

359
00:16:38,461 --> 00:16:39,968
they're coming.

360
00:16:40,003 --> 00:16:41,540
Who?

361
00:16:49,683 --> 00:16:50,731
Listen to me, Joe.

362
00:16:50,766 --> 00:16:52,120
Listen very carefully.

363
00:16:52,155 --> 00:16:54,052
They destroyed our world,

364
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:56,487
and they'll destroy yours.

365
00:16:56,489 --> 00:17:00,425
This isn't just about the
survival of the kinship.

366
00:17:00,427 --> 00:17:03,261
It's about humanity's
survival, too.

367
00:17:03,263 --> 00:17:06,381
Whether you want to
recognize it or not,

368
00:17:06,416 --> 00:17:09,367
our fates are tied together.

369
00:17:09,369 --> 00:17:14,046
And the only way
we stand a chance

370
00:17:14,081 --> 00:17:16,784
is for us to get
out of this dome.

371
00:17:19,345 --> 00:17:23,457
That rests entirely
in your hands.

372
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:32,251
My poor father.

373
00:17:33,094 --> 00:17:35,559
I failed him.

374
00:17:35,561 --> 00:17:36,993
I never should've given up.

375
00:17:36,995 --> 00:17:38,762
No, Lily,

376
00:17:38,764 --> 00:17:41,331
this is not your fault.

377
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,521
Okay?
This one's on Hektor.

378
00:17:43,556 --> 00:17:46,363
He's been like
a second father to me.

379
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:49,072
How am I supposed
to trust him now?

380
00:17:49,107 --> 00:17:51,136
Look, I don't know him,

381
00:17:51,171 --> 00:17:53,412
and I'm not usually
the type to make excuses

382
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:55,131
for corporate
billionaire overlords,

383
00:17:55,166 --> 00:17:58,946
but maybe he had
good intentions.

384
00:17:59,015 --> 00:18:02,562
I'm just saying Hektor
can't be all bad.

385
00:18:02,597 --> 00:18:04,898
He came in here
to help us, right?

386
00:18:04,933 --> 00:18:07,590
Get us secure and
get this dome down.

387
00:18:07,592 --> 00:18:09,981
Right, Lily?

388
00:18:10,294 --> 00:18:11,653
Of course.

389
00:18:11,688 --> 00:18:13,896
Of course that's what
he's doing.

390
00:18:14,965 --> 00:18:18,856
I'm sorry, I just need time
to process all this.

391
00:18:23,327 --> 00:18:24,745
Come on, kiddo.

392
00:18:24,780 --> 00:18:26,855
You got to fight through it.

393
00:18:27,543 --> 00:18:29,731
This cure of yours
is burning him up.

394
00:18:29,766 --> 00:18:32,163
Be patient, Jim;
it's a good sign.

395
00:18:32,415 --> 00:18:34,450
106-degree fever
is a good sign?

396
00:18:34,485 --> 00:18:36,425
What, do you think brain
damage is a good thing, too?

397
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:37,903
The fact that he's running
a high fever means

398
00:18:37,938 --> 00:18:39,888
that his body is responding
properly to the virus.

399
00:18:39,890 --> 00:18:42,371
Just... just give it
time, okay?

400
00:18:42,556 --> 00:18:43,758
Excuse me.

401
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,900
I don't know what to do.

402
00:18:50,586 --> 00:18:53,435
Lily?

403
00:18:53,437 --> 00:18:54,855
I was just trying
to protect you.

404
00:18:54,890 --> 00:18:56,774
- From my father?
- Not from him.

405
00:18:56,809 --> 00:18:58,339
From what he became.

406
00:18:58,341 --> 00:18:59,942
I don't want your
memory of Patrick

407
00:18:59,977 --> 00:19:02,136
to be corrupted.

408
00:19:02,171 --> 00:19:04,116
That wasn't
your decision to make.

409
00:19:04,151 --> 00:19:05,446
I know it wasn't,

410
00:19:05,448 --> 00:19:07,415
and I'm sorry.

411
00:19:07,417 --> 00:19:10,452
I just thought if I
could find a cure,

412
00:19:10,487 --> 00:19:13,891
I could return him whole
to you, the man you knew.

413
00:19:13,926 --> 00:19:15,297
Everything that I've
done since it happened

414
00:19:15,332 --> 00:19:16,960
has been toward that end.

415
00:19:16,995 --> 00:19:18,090
I didn't tell you he was alive

416
00:19:18,125 --> 00:19:21,381
because I didn't want
to give you false hope.

417
00:19:23,765 --> 00:19:26,900
I've got to ask:

418
00:19:26,902 --> 00:19:29,993
How did they get the video?

419
00:19:30,905 --> 00:19:33,737
I sent the files through.

420
00:19:33,772 --> 00:19:35,371
I told you to destroy them.

421
00:19:35,406 --> 00:19:35,976
I know.

422
00:19:36,011 --> 00:19:37,587
The reason why the
government wants us dead

423
00:19:37,622 --> 00:19:39,249
is in those files.

424
00:19:39,284 --> 00:19:41,836
If the truth got out about
what's really under this dome,

425
00:19:41,871 --> 00:19:43,858
there'd be a situation
that they couldn't control.

426
00:19:43,893 --> 00:19:46,088
Easier to bury the evidence
and hide the bodies.

427
00:19:46,123 --> 00:19:48,055
That's why we can't
ever leave, Lily.

428
00:19:48,090 --> 00:19:50,003
No. This information
about my father,

429
00:19:50,038 --> 00:19:51,749
it changes everything.

430
00:19:51,784 --> 00:19:53,582
Especially if the cure works.

431
00:19:53,617 --> 00:19:54,727
- Lily...
- Shut up

432
00:19:54,729 --> 00:19:56,029
and listen to me.

433
00:19:56,031 --> 00:19:57,663
Say it works,

434
00:19:57,665 --> 00:19:59,399
and you save all these people.

435
00:19:59,401 --> 00:20:02,202
And say what
Jim told you is true,

436
00:20:02,204 --> 00:20:04,269
that there is a way
out of the dome.

437
00:20:04,271 --> 00:20:07,553
You could walk
out of here a hero.

438
00:20:07,588 --> 00:20:09,541
The government
couldn't touch you.

439
00:20:09,543 --> 00:20:11,902
And those files?

440
00:20:13,079 --> 00:20:15,514
Just an insurance policy.

441
00:20:16,849 --> 00:20:20,277
I need to see my father again.

442
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:23,601
You owe that to me.

443
00:20:28,528 --> 00:20:30,228
All right, Lily.

444
00:20:31,531 --> 00:20:35,298
If the cure works,
I'll... I'll get us out.

445
00:20:39,005 --> 00:20:41,272
Eva?

446
00:20:41,274 --> 00:20:42,641
What's wrong?
You in pain?

447
00:20:42,643 --> 00:20:44,108
No. No pain at all.

448
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:46,609
Good. Here you go.

449
00:20:56,021 --> 00:20:57,121
What?

450
00:20:57,123 --> 00:20:58,423
Nothing.

451
00:20:58,425 --> 00:21:01,125
Eva... what is it?

452
00:21:01,127 --> 00:21:03,794
Talk to me.

453
00:21:05,196 --> 00:21:05,932
It's just...

454
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:08,131
all of this is

455
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:09,633
happening so fast.

456
00:21:09,635 --> 00:21:11,234
I'm not sure I'm ready.

457
00:21:11,236 --> 00:21:15,104
I mean, what if I let the
kinship... or you... down?

458
00:21:15,139 --> 00:21:17,171
Why would you think that?

459
00:21:19,311 --> 00:21:22,004
There is nothing
you can't tell me.

460
00:21:26,850 --> 00:21:31,568
My earliest memory...

461
00:21:31,603 --> 00:21:34,691
I couldn't have been
more than four...

462
00:21:34,693 --> 00:21:36,498
is of blood.

463
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:38,428
A drop of blood
on a shattered piece

464
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:40,699
of my mother's
family china.

465
00:21:40,734 --> 00:21:43,200
She'd thrown it
at my dad.

466
00:21:43,202 --> 00:21:47,431
I don't even know what
they were arguing about...

467
00:21:47,466 --> 00:21:50,301
but I'll never forget
that drop of blood.

468
00:21:52,910 --> 00:21:56,995
A broken piece of him
on a broken piece of her.

469
00:22:00,751 --> 00:22:01,972
Not long after that,

470
00:22:02,007 --> 00:22:05,053
my parents and I,
we spent a summer

471
00:22:05,088 --> 00:22:06,060
in a mountain cabin

472
00:22:06,095 --> 00:22:08,507
outside of
Salt Lake City.

473
00:22:09,794 --> 00:22:12,661
And it was just
the three of us,

474
00:22:12,663 --> 00:22:14,029
and the woods

475
00:22:14,031 --> 00:22:16,197
and the birds...

476
00:22:23,205 --> 00:22:24,849
And... and...

477
00:22:24,884 --> 00:22:26,842
that was the happiest time
of my life.

478
00:22:26,844 --> 00:22:30,290
And then we came back
to the real world.

479
00:22:30,325 --> 00:22:33,581
My parents were divorced
within a year.

480
00:22:35,784 --> 00:22:39,041
I don't want that for our baby.

481
00:22:40,822 --> 00:22:42,423
I want the cabin.

482
00:22:42,458 --> 00:22:44,773
And I want the three of us
to be together forever.

483
00:22:44,808 --> 00:22:46,661
You can have that, Eva.

484
00:22:46,663 --> 00:22:47,408
What are you talking about?

485
00:22:47,443 --> 00:22:50,197
I am talking about
getting out of here.

486
00:22:50,199 --> 00:22:51,562
About running away.

487
00:22:51,597 --> 00:22:52,906
I-I don't know how...

488
00:22:52,941 --> 00:22:53,889
we'll figure that out.

489
00:22:53,924 --> 00:22:57,177
But just you and me,
our baby...

490
00:22:59,073 --> 00:23:00,874
I knew it.

491
00:23:02,043 --> 00:23:05,374
I knew you weren't
one of us.

492
00:23:06,413 --> 00:23:09,091
Julia is still alive, isn't she?

493
00:23:09,884 --> 00:23:11,918
I bet she's...

494
00:23:19,259 --> 00:23:20,959
What did you put
in the tea?

495
00:23:20,961 --> 00:23:22,895
I had to, Eva.

496
00:23:24,097 --> 00:23:26,732
I'm not gonna let you
hurt my baby.

497
00:23:55,736 --> 00:23:57,235
Have you made
up your mind?

498
00:23:57,270 --> 00:23:59,568
Are you going to help us
take down the dome?

499
00:23:59,603 --> 00:24:02,272
I don't really
have a choice, do I?

500
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:03,657
Neither of us do.

501
00:24:03,659 --> 00:24:05,725
The real trick'll be doing
the calculations necessary

502
00:24:05,727 --> 00:24:08,245
to split the amethyst
into seven pieces.

503
00:24:09,978 --> 00:24:11,825
Are you okay?

504
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:13,728
In truth...

505
00:24:13,763 --> 00:24:17,089
I'm dying.

506
00:24:17,124 --> 00:24:19,797
My cycle's coming to an end.

507
00:24:19,832 --> 00:24:22,675
Just as it must.

508
00:24:22,677 --> 00:24:24,568
My work is almost done.

509
00:24:24,603 --> 00:24:26,927
As soon as the
dome comes down...

510
00:24:26,962 --> 00:24:29,676
Well, I'll work
as fast as I can.

511
00:24:34,288 --> 00:24:35,721
How's it looking?

512
00:24:35,723 --> 00:24:37,056
Promising.

513
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:39,257
Very promising.

514
00:24:47,734 --> 00:24:49,776
Dad... Where are we?

515
00:24:49,811 --> 00:24:53,104
You're in a safe place.

516
00:24:53,106 --> 00:24:54,138
How you feel?

517
00:24:54,140 --> 00:24:55,385
Like I'm on fire.

518
00:24:55,420 --> 00:24:57,675
But... I'm awake.

519
00:24:57,677 --> 00:24:59,877
What do you remember?

520
00:25:01,046 --> 00:25:02,647
All of it.

521
00:25:04,216 --> 00:25:06,718
Thanks for not giving up on me.

522
00:25:08,553 --> 00:25:11,103
You went through
the wringer, kid.

523
00:25:11,511 --> 00:25:14,692
A lot tougher than
I gave you credit for.

524
00:25:18,030 --> 00:25:20,463
I'm gonna promise you
something right now.

525
00:25:20,465 --> 00:25:22,792
When this dome comes down...

526
00:25:22,827 --> 00:25:26,803
and it will come down...

527
00:25:26,805 --> 00:25:29,314
everything's gonna be different.

528
00:25:31,142 --> 00:25:33,443
You and me,

529
00:25:33,445 --> 00:25:37,340
we're gonna start over,
just the two of us.

530
00:25:37,375 --> 00:25:40,283
Maybe we can work
together at the lot.

531
00:25:40,285 --> 00:25:43,038
"Rennie and Son""

532
00:25:43,073 --> 00:25:46,122
How does that sound?

533
00:25:46,124 --> 00:25:48,791
Sounds good.

534
00:25:48,793 --> 00:25:51,030
Except for the used cars part.

535
00:25:51,065 --> 00:25:52,728
Does it have
to be used cars?

536
00:25:52,730 --> 00:25:53,996
Nah,

537
00:25:53,998 --> 00:25:56,232
it can be
whatever you like.

538
00:25:56,234 --> 00:25:59,802
Important thing...

539
00:25:59,804 --> 00:26:02,745
is that it's you and me.

540
00:26:07,978 --> 00:26:10,294
These... these
restraints too tight?

541
00:26:10,329 --> 00:26:11,680
No. That's okay.

542
00:26:11,682 --> 00:26:14,125
I get why they're there.

543
00:26:15,385 --> 00:26:17,676
All right.

544
00:26:17,711 --> 00:26:20,822
I'll see if I can,
wrangle up some pop.

545
00:26:29,130 --> 00:26:32,099
Wanted to give this back.

546
00:26:32,101 --> 00:26:34,405
I was wondering
where that went.

547
00:26:35,377 --> 00:26:36,470
Nah, keep it.

548
00:26:36,472 --> 00:26:38,470
I got plenty.

549
00:26:40,075 --> 00:26:42,360
Something else?

550
00:26:44,445 --> 00:26:47,080
What did it feel like...

551
00:26:47,082 --> 00:26:49,381
when you first killed somebody?

552
00:26:53,020 --> 00:26:56,011
It gets easier
the more you do it.

553
00:26:56,046 --> 00:26:57,805
As far as I recall,
I never bagged anyone

554
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:59,401
who didn't bear
some responsibility

555
00:26:59,436 --> 00:27:01,190
for the getting killed part.

556
00:27:01,225 --> 00:27:03,761
Why?
You feeling guilty?

557
00:27:04,898 --> 00:27:06,597
Well, that's the thing.

558
00:27:06,632 --> 00:27:08,801
I don't.

559
00:27:08,803 --> 00:27:12,374
I don't feel anything at all.

560
00:27:34,295 --> 00:27:35,376
Of course Junior's not here

561
00:27:35,379 --> 00:27:36,962
when all the heavy lifting
needs to be done.

562
00:27:36,964 --> 00:27:38,397
I haven't seen him all day.

563
00:27:38,399 --> 00:27:39,365
Me, neither.

564
00:27:39,367 --> 00:27:40,666
Not since last night.

565
00:27:40,668 --> 00:27:42,684
Last night?

566
00:27:43,810 --> 00:27:46,582
Look, I've probably
said too much already,

567
00:27:46,617 --> 00:27:48,513
especially considering
Junior outranks me.

568
00:27:48,548 --> 00:27:50,024
I do, too.

569
00:27:50,059 --> 00:27:51,477
So what were you doing
last night?

570
00:27:55,581 --> 00:27:57,724
Junior doesn't trust Barbie,

571
00:27:57,759 --> 00:28:00,801
so we went to
Peter Shumway's cabin.

572
00:28:04,056 --> 00:28:05,890
I'm sorry to disturb you,

573
00:28:05,892 --> 00:28:08,880
but... we have
a problem.

574
00:28:17,134 --> 00:28:18,511
Julia?

575
00:28:18,546 --> 00:28:20,151
You there?

576
00:28:23,635 --> 00:28:24,775
Hey, I'm here.

577
00:28:24,777 --> 00:28:26,557
Hey, I've got Eva.

578
00:28:26,592 --> 00:28:27,881
I couldn't save her.

579
00:28:27,916 --> 00:28:29,818
I tried to, but...

580
00:28:29,853 --> 00:28:31,481
but it didn't work.

581
00:28:31,483 --> 00:28:33,361
What are you gonna do now?

582
00:28:33,396 --> 00:28:36,045
I'm going to stay with her
till she gives birth.

583
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:36,885
I couldn't save Eva,

584
00:28:36,887 --> 00:28:39,087
but at least
I can save my child.

585
00:28:39,089 --> 00:28:40,155
Come meet us.
We're at the...

586
00:28:40,157 --> 00:28:41,457
No, no, no, no.

587
00:28:41,459 --> 00:28:42,825
What?

588
00:28:44,094 --> 00:28:45,679
- Don't.
- He's not one of them.

589
00:28:45,714 --> 00:28:46,747
And what if he is?

590
00:28:46,782 --> 00:28:47,554
He might be trying
to get you

591
00:28:47,589 --> 00:28:49,298
to reveal our location.

592
00:28:51,369 --> 00:28:52,368
Julia?

593
00:28:52,370 --> 00:28:54,069
Are you there?

594
00:28:54,071 --> 00:28:55,938
Yeah, I think
she's going into labor.

595
00:28:55,940 --> 00:28:57,206
The motel.

596
00:28:57,208 --> 00:28:58,294
Meet me there.

597
00:28:58,329 --> 00:29:00,094
All right. Hurry!

598
00:29:01,077 --> 00:29:04,273
They won't give that baby up
without a fight.

599
00:29:11,069 --> 00:29:13,073
- Hey.
- Where's Barbie and Eva?

600
00:29:13,108 --> 00:29:14,409
They're nowhere
to be found.

601
00:29:14,444 --> 00:29:16,511
And the car's missing, as well.

602
00:29:16,964 --> 00:29:18,960
Organize the town.
Everyone.

603
00:29:18,995 --> 00:29:21,155
Fan out and
find them. Now!

604
00:29:21,190 --> 00:29:23,190
Let's go.

605
00:29:30,616 --> 00:29:32,186
That should be it.

606
00:29:32,221 --> 00:29:33,669
You want me to drill these?

607
00:29:33,704 --> 00:29:35,017
Yeah.

608
00:29:35,052 --> 00:29:37,387
Four inches deep.

609
00:29:37,389 --> 00:29:38,922
Was something unclear?

610
00:29:38,924 --> 00:29:41,124
No, it's just...

611
00:29:41,159 --> 00:29:42,593
this is our last amethyst.

612
00:29:42,595 --> 00:29:43,701
If you're wrong...

613
00:29:43,736 --> 00:29:45,095
I'm not.

614
00:29:45,097 --> 00:29:46,096
Start drilling.

615
00:30:01,291 --> 00:30:02,204
Take me back.

616
00:30:02,239 --> 00:30:03,094
No. Lay down.

617
00:30:03,129 --> 00:30:04,980
You're not going anywhere.

618
00:30:09,186 --> 00:30:11,387
Sit on up.

619
00:30:15,726 --> 00:30:18,640
I knew she wasn't dead,
you coward!

620
00:30:21,497 --> 00:30:23,125
Anybody follow you?

621
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:26,001
No, but it'll only be a matter
of time before they find us.

622
00:30:26,003 --> 00:30:28,053
We just have to hope
that baby comes first.

623
00:30:28,088 --> 00:30:29,504
I'm gonna say something
you don't want to hear.

624
00:30:29,506 --> 00:30:30,469
We should leave.

625
00:30:30,504 --> 00:30:32,207
No, Julia. No way.

626
00:30:32,209 --> 00:30:33,942
I know this is hard.

627
00:30:33,944 --> 00:30:35,263
But the kinship's
not gonna stop

628
00:30:35,298 --> 00:30:36,611
until they have their queen.

629
00:30:36,613 --> 00:30:38,703
That baby is half mine.

630
00:30:38,738 --> 00:30:41,016
As long as there's even a chance
that she is more me than them,

631
00:30:41,018 --> 00:30:42,600
I'm not gonna abandon her.

632
00:30:42,635 --> 00:30:44,154
I can't.

633
00:30:44,189 --> 00:30:46,555
Well, we're about to
find out if you're right.

634
00:30:51,536 --> 00:30:53,528
Sorry for barking at you before.

635
00:30:53,530 --> 00:30:55,630
No need apologize.

636
00:30:55,632 --> 00:30:56,997
I can't imagine what it's like

637
00:30:57,032 --> 00:30:58,897
watching your child
go through that.

638
00:30:58,932 --> 00:31:00,216
Yeah, anyway,

639
00:31:00,251 --> 00:31:02,574
I... I wanted to thank you

640
00:31:02,609 --> 00:31:05,428
for giving me back my son.

641
00:31:05,463 --> 00:31:06,608
Well...

642
00:31:06,610 --> 00:31:08,510
don't thank me yet.

643
00:31:08,512 --> 00:31:09,811
Why? It worked.

644
00:31:09,813 --> 00:31:12,565
He's himself again.

645
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:14,680
I actually was gonna
ask you if we could

646
00:31:14,715 --> 00:31:17,299
lose the restraints.

647
00:31:17,334 --> 00:31:17,888
Jim...

648
00:31:17,923 --> 00:31:19,222
the signs look good.

649
00:31:19,257 --> 00:31:20,689
But we have
to continue monitoring him

650
00:31:20,691 --> 00:31:23,257
for the time being.

651
00:31:24,092 --> 00:31:26,183
All right.

652
00:31:29,297 --> 00:31:32,477
When will the cure be ready
for the rest of the town?

653
00:31:32,512 --> 00:31:34,599
When I say it's ready.

654
00:31:40,711 --> 00:31:42,326
Shouldn't have baby
been here by now?

655
00:31:42,361 --> 00:31:43,633
I don't know.

656
00:31:43,668 --> 00:31:45,912
I don't know why...

657
00:31:46,781 --> 00:31:50,101
Unless...

658
00:31:52,486 --> 00:31:55,188
You hoping you can hold off
until Christine finds you?

659
00:31:55,223 --> 00:31:56,822
Get away from me, bitch.

660
00:31:58,493 --> 00:32:00,660
I can't believe
I'm gonna do this.

661
00:32:00,662 --> 00:32:02,614
I'm helping you deliver
your baby with another woman.

662
00:32:02,649 --> 00:32:05,428
I know.
Eva, you need to push.

663
00:32:05,463 --> 00:32:07,099
No.

664
00:32:08,303 --> 00:32:09,311
Push now!

665
00:32:09,346 --> 00:32:10,270
No!

666
00:32:12,105 --> 00:32:13,505
No!

667
00:32:15,142 --> 00:32:17,243
All right.

668
00:32:17,977 --> 00:32:19,478
Okay, keep going.

669
00:32:20,914 --> 00:32:22,142
Julia!

670
00:32:22,177 --> 00:32:23,448
- Damn it.
- The baby!

671
00:32:24,851 --> 00:32:27,018
Here it comes.

672
00:32:30,022 --> 00:32:31,529
Okay, okay.

673
00:32:31,564 --> 00:32:34,092
Okay, okay...

674
00:32:46,806 --> 00:32:49,882
I know, I know.

675
00:32:55,512 --> 00:32:57,815
Hey, it's Daddy.

676
00:32:57,817 --> 00:33:00,017
Yeah.

677
00:33:01,987 --> 00:33:04,153
One last step.

678
00:33:04,155 --> 00:33:05,622
You sure this
is going to work?

679
00:33:05,624 --> 00:33:08,309
Only one way to find out.

680
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:31,814
Here you go.

681
00:33:31,816 --> 00:33:33,706
Oh, this is ridiculous.

682
00:33:33,741 --> 00:33:34,583
It's okay.

683
00:33:34,585 --> 00:33:37,353
No, it's not.
It's not okay.

684
00:33:37,355 --> 00:33:41,523
You do not need to be tied up
like an animal.

685
00:33:48,431 --> 00:33:51,032
Thanks, Dad.

686
00:33:51,868 --> 00:33:54,941
But you shouldn't
have done that.

687
00:34:03,946 --> 00:34:05,790
That's cute.

688
00:34:19,060 --> 00:34:20,961
Too tight for you?

689
00:34:20,963 --> 00:34:22,501
Wait, scratch that.

690
00:34:22,536 --> 00:34:24,965
I don't care.

691
00:34:38,413 --> 00:34:40,680
It's time to go.

692
00:34:40,682 --> 00:34:44,847
Hey, let me hold her.

693
00:34:44,882 --> 00:34:46,453
Dale...

694
00:34:46,455 --> 00:34:48,755
look at me.

695
00:34:48,757 --> 00:34:50,656
If you're gonna take her
away from me forever,

696
00:34:50,691 --> 00:34:51,758
let me hold her.

697
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:54,465
Just once.

698
00:34:55,763 --> 00:34:58,559
She needs to be fed.

699
00:35:01,136 --> 00:35:02,769
Please, Dale.

700
00:35:02,771 --> 00:35:04,939
It's up to you.

701
00:35:23,858 --> 00:35:26,628
Barbie, we've got company.

702
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:42,808
Get the baby.

703
00:35:44,511 --> 00:35:46,490
Eva?

704
00:35:52,453 --> 00:35:54,620
Give her to me now.

705
00:36:03,396 --> 00:36:05,559
She's not yours.

706
00:36:09,848 --> 00:36:12,308
She is my queen.

707
00:36:16,175 --> 00:36:17,910
Barbie! Barbie...

708
00:36:17,912 --> 00:36:19,077
Oh, my God.

709
00:36:19,079 --> 00:36:20,525
You okay?
Can you get up?

710
00:36:20,560 --> 00:36:22,418
Come on. Come on.

711
00:36:22,453 --> 00:36:24,323
We gotta go.

712
00:36:24,817 --> 00:36:26,351
I'm not leaving
my daughter.

713
00:36:26,353 --> 00:36:29,165
Whatever that thing is,
it is not your daughter!

714
00:36:35,461 --> 00:36:38,063
Barbie, if we stay here,

715
00:36:38,065 --> 00:36:39,831
we die.

716
00:36:41,167 --> 00:36:43,252
Come on.

717
00:36:48,007 --> 00:36:50,875
So much for your miracle cure.

718
00:36:50,877 --> 00:36:53,578
Whatever's inside him
is mutating too quickly

719
00:36:53,580 --> 00:36:56,213
to target and eliminate.

720
00:36:56,215 --> 00:36:58,149
It's like...

721
00:36:58,151 --> 00:37:00,852
it's smarter
than the treatment.

722
00:37:00,854 --> 00:37:03,741
And I know this can work,
given the time, I...

723
00:37:05,624 --> 00:37:08,217
Except we're out of time.

724
00:37:10,629 --> 00:37:12,797
Listen to me, Jim.

725
00:37:12,799 --> 00:37:16,366
We don't have a choice.

726
00:37:16,368 --> 00:37:20,222
We have to kill them all.

727
00:37:21,539 --> 00:37:23,974
Everyone that's carrying
the infection.

728
00:37:23,976 --> 00:37:25,969
Including
the dormant ones:

729
00:37:26,004 --> 00:37:27,453
Hunter, Norrie, Joe,

730
00:37:27,488 --> 00:37:29,412
Barbie, everyone.

731
00:37:29,414 --> 00:37:31,081
It's the only
way to make sure

732
00:37:31,083 --> 00:37:34,117
that the Life Force never
gets outside of this dome.

733
00:37:37,822 --> 00:37:40,461
Are you all right with that?

734
00:37:45,262 --> 00:37:47,899
Sure.

735
00:37:54,838 --> 00:37:57,224
What is it, Lily?

736
00:38:10,353 --> 00:38:13,656
Give us some privacy.

737
00:38:30,206 --> 00:38:33,132
I'm so proud of you.

738
00:38:34,061 --> 00:38:36,845
Look at what a good job
you've done.

739
00:38:45,821 --> 00:38:48,969
She's taking
what she needs.

740
00:39:14,082 --> 00:39:17,485
What's happening?

741
00:39:17,487 --> 00:39:19,853
Where am I?

742
00:39:19,855 --> 00:39:22,496
Is that my baby?

743
00:39:23,858 --> 00:39:26,760
What are you doing
with my baby?

744
00:39:26,762 --> 00:39:29,455
She's not your baby.

745
00:39:31,532 --> 00:39:35,001
And you're no longer
one of us.

746
00:39:36,694 --> 00:39:40,431
♪ Lullaby and good night ♪

747
00:39:40,466 --> 00:39:43,780
♪ Thy mother's delight ♪

748
00:39:43,815 --> 00:39:47,614
♪ Bright angel beside ♪

749
00:39:47,616 --> 00:39:51,196
♪ My darling abide ♪

750
00:39:51,231 --> 00:39:54,872
♪ Lay thee down now and rest ♪

751
00:39:54,907 --> 00:39:58,909
♪ May thy slumber be blessed ♪

752
00:39:58,944 --> 00:40:02,730
♪ Lay thee down now and rest ♪

753
00:40:02,765 --> 00:40:08,166
♪ May thy slumber be blessed... ♪

754
00:40:11,074 --> 00:40:14,797
♪ With roses bedight thee ♪

755
00:40:14,832 --> 00:40:18,844
♪ With lilies over spread ♪

756
00:40:18,846 --> 00:40:23,287
♪ This baby's wee bed ♪

757
00:40:23,322 --> 00:40:27,029
♪ Lay thee down now and rest ♪

758
00:40:27,064 --> 00:40:30,766
♪ May thy slumber be blessed... ♪
